PS1='\u@\h:\w\[\e[1;31m\]\$ \[\e[m\]'
The command set red bold color of dollar sign in bash prompt.

1;31 part set color and style (style;color)
Style:
 0 - default
 1 - bold
 2 - thin
 3 - italic
 4 - underlined
 7 - reverse
 8 - hidden
 9 - crossed
Color:
 39 - default
 30 - black
 31 - red
 32 - green
 33 - yellow
 34 - blue
 35 - purple
 36 - cyan
 37 - light gray

u - user
h - host
w - path
